/**
 * bioscan.js
 *
 * DEAD SIGNAL — Deterministic BIO-SCAN engine for the Hargrove interview.
 *
 * BIO-SCAN readouts are NOT generated by an LLM. They are an authored,
 * topic-keyed data table (a golden dataset of expected instrument outputs).
 * The interview's current topic state selects one row; the HUD renders it in
 * cyan. Keeping this deterministic makes the readouts consistent, controllable,
 * free, and — for the eval harness — a curated set of expected outputs the
 * topic classifier can be scored against.
 *
 * Locked topic set (LOCKED DECISION ADDENDUM §9):
 *   default · courier_manifest · chip_donation · clinical_trial_st_erasmus ·
 *   celeste_grief · unprompted_denial · interference_conflict
 *
 * Each row also carries:
 *   - frame:  which Hargrove image to show (§12). Only two frames exist:
 *             'composed' (executive calm) and 'pressure' (subtle defensive
 *             tension). The map below is the FULL topic→frame pinning the
 *             addendum left half-specified.
 *   - lesson: which of the four required interpretive lessons (§10) this row
 *             teaches. The debrief and the eval harness read this to show that
 *             BIO-SCAN stress != deception, etc.
 */

